Package com.nickbenn.onehundred.controller

Class Referee

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.nickbenn.onehundred.controller.Referee
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    ConsoleSolitaireReferee
    public abstract class Referee
extends Object
    Encapsulates the enforcement of the rules of the game, along with updates to the game state. In this abstract class, no assumptions are made regarding the UI mechanisms; a concrete subclass must coordinate any necessary user interaction functionality, leveraging a GamePresentation<T> instance, provided via the Builder(GamePresentation) instantiation.

      • play

        public void play()
        Orchestrates the changes of state and user interaction through completion of a single Game, using an instance of GamePresentation<T> provided via Builder(GamePresentation). In many cases, there will be no need to override this method.

      • presentState

        protected abstract void presentState()
        Presents the current state of the game, incorporating content provided by the encapsulated GamePresentation<T>. A concrete subclass must implement this method appropriately for the user interaction mode employed by that subclass, with view objects of subtypes of that specified in the GamePresentation<T> type parameter.

      • applyMove

        protected void applyMove​(int move)
        Updates the state of the current Game instance, according to the specified move. Under most conditions, this method need not be overridden; if it is, it should be invoked by the overriding method.
        Parameters:
        move - Number added to (or subtracted from) the total.

      • presentCompletedMove

        protected abstract void presentCompletedMove​(Game.State state,
                                             int move)
        Presents the most recently completed move, incorporating content provided by the encapsulated GamePresentation<T>. A concrete subclass must implement this method appropriately for the user interaction mode employed by that subclass, with view objects of subtypes of that specified in the GamePresentation<T> type parameter.
        Parameters:
        state - Game.State resulting from the completed move.
        move - Most recent addition (or subtraction).

      • presentError

A concrete subclass must implement this method appropriately for the user interaction mode employed by that subclass, with view objects of subtypes of that specified in the GamePresentation<T> type parameter.
        Parameters:
